Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 1. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.

Defendant Elijah V Kimbrough appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Dean Douglas Sopcic appeared by video for Elijah V Kimbrough.  Prosecuting attorney Katrina Voge appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
Doctor's Report Return hearing held. Defendant was found competent. Parties do not contest the results of the report. Court adopts the courts findings into the record. Defense requests a NGI evaluation. Case adjourned to Branch 1.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for November 17, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Forensic evaluation ordered.  INITIAL APPEARANCE NOT HELD.  Trial court to address INITIAL APPEARANCE.

Defendant Elijah V Kimbrough appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke appeared by video for Elijah V Kimbrough. Attorney Arthur Kenneth Thexton appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 1. Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for October 18, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
